@page "/compose"

<PageTitle>Compose</PageTitle>

<div class="space-y-6">
    <header class="space-y-3">
        <div>
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-signal-600">Downlink</p>
            <h1 class="font-display text-4xl text-cinder-950 sm:text-5xl">Message composition</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="max-w-5xl text-base leading-8 text-cinder-800">
            Compose is intentionally deferred while the browser-first realtime path replaces the legacy server runtime.
        </p>
    </header>

    <section class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr]">
        <article class="liquid-panel rounded-[1.6rem] p-6">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-cinder-950">Deferred</h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-cinder-800/82">
                The legacy server-side send path is being retired. This page stays read-only until the future outbound
                design is implemented on top of the browser vault and worker contracts.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-6 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-cinder-800/85">
                <li>No plaintext downlink flow remains active in the Blazor Server UI.</li>
                <li>Browser-local keys and worker contracts are being kept compatible with a future outbound design.</li>
                <li>Broker profiles, presets, favorites, and saved channels now live in the new browser-first flow.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="liquid-panel rounded-[1.6rem] p-6">
            <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-cinder-950">Migration Notes</h2>
            <dl class="mt-4 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-[9rem_1fr] text-sm">
                <dt class="text-cinder-800/70">Current state</dt>
                <dd class="text-cinder-950">Send is disabled in the legacy server-rendered application.</dd>
                <dt class="text-cinder-800/70">Target path</dt>
                <dd class="text-cinder-950">Browser client, local key vault, worker-side crypto, and broker-issued realtime sessions.</dd>
                <dt class="text-cinder-800/70">Next step</dt>
                <dd class="text-cinder-950">Compose will return only after the outbound trust model has a dedicated ADR and implementation slice.</dd>
            </dl>
        </article>
    </section>
</div>
